description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Title: Ward Administrator&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Grade: Band 3&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Care Group 2a Part Time (19hrs) Moreton Ward Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you a highly motivated individual or looking for your next opportunity as an administrator? We may have what you are looking for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Within the Integrated and Holistic Care Group two Ward Administrator posts have become available to support our busy Ward Sisters.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for supporting the Ward Sister in administrative tasks to assist in the management of their team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The care group can support you in opportunities to develop and enhance your skills including NVQ Business Administration skills within fast paced and supportive ward environments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Moreton ward cares for patients with Respiratory conditions and General Medicine.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will…..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide support to the Ward Sister and the ward team in administrative duties to progress the day to day running of the ward&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively manage the business of the ward with the Ward Sister&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You have…..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administrative experience and skills in a healthcare setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are familiar with office programmes such as Microsoft Outlook, Excel and Word as well as the Trusts’ Patient Administration System, Digital Patient Record, Datix and the staff E-roster system&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good communication skills and can engage with the multidisciplinary team effectively&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The ability to use your own initiative and make informed decisions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We can offer you…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support, to develop you with the Ward Sister, in the administration of the Ward, the Staff and the setting up of meetings on behalf of the Ward Sister, as well as taking an active part in the management of ward risks&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support to develop business and administrative skills and experience needed for further progression within an interesting and varied role&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Further education such as NVQ Education and training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible working to ensure all staff have a successful work/life balance dependant on the requirements of the service&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a Trust that celebrates diversity and we are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. We would welcome applications from people in groups which are under-represented in our organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: Midnight 8th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interviews: 17th November 2020 &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Name: Lynn Paterson Job title: Ward Sister Email address: Lynn.Paterson@dchft.nhs.uk Telephone number: 01305 2544358&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
